==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disulphate
<hw>Di*sul"phate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>di-</ets> + <ets>sulphate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A salt of disulphuric or pyrosulphuric acid; a
pyrosulphate.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An acid salt of sulphuric acid,
having only one equivalent of base to two of the acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disulphide</ent>⟦br⟧
